  "bodyPreview": "INSTRUCTIONS:\n\n\nKindly fill the form and click the 'Save as PDF' Button.The 'RESET' Button clears all the fields you have filled-in, so you can start over.\nOnce Saved as PDF you will not be able to make changes.\nUpon clicking 'Save as PDF', a PDF copy of your form will be downloaded, which can be printed, emailed or uploaded to another application.\n\nMPC 550 (10/23/12)  NTCIP\nof\npage\nSave as PDF\nReset Form\nDocket No.\nNOTICE OF INFORMAL PROBATE\nCommonwealth of Massachusetts \nThe Trial Court \n Probate and Family Court\nFirst Name\nLast Name\nMiddle Name\nEstate of:\nG.L. c. 190B, § 3-306\nAlso Known As:\nDate of Death:\n Division\nBarnstable\nBerkshire\nBristol\nDukes\nEssex\nFranklin\nHampden\nHampshire\nMiddlesex\nNantucket\nNorfolk\nPlymouth\nSuffolk\nWorcester\nTo all persons who have or may have some interest in the above-captioned estate and, if interested, to the Office of the \nAttorney General and the Department of Veterans Affairs, notice is hereby given on\n(date)\nthat the Petitioner\nFirst Name\nM.I.\nLast Name\n(City/Town)\n(State)\nof\nclick to add\nclick to remove\nintends to file with the above-named Probate and Family Court, not sooner than seven (7) days after this notice, a\nPetition for Informal Probate of a Will\nPetition for Informal Appointment of Personal Representative, to serve \nwithout surety on the bond\n with\nFirst Name\nM.I.\nLast Name\n(City/Town)\n(State)\nof\nclick to add\nclick to remove\nThe estate is being administered under informal procedure by the Personal Representative under the Massachusetts Uniform \nProbate Code without supervision by the Court.  Inventory and accounts are not required to be filed with the Court, but \ninterested parties are entitled to notice regarding the administration from the Personal Representative and can petition the \nCourt in any matter relating to the estate, including distribution of assets and expenses of administration.  Interested parties \nare entitled to petition the Court to institute formal proceedings and to obtain orders terminating or restricting the powers of \nPersonal Representatives appointed under informal procedure. A copy of the Petition and Will, if any, can be obtained from \nthe Petitioner.\nMPC 550 (10/23/12)  NTCIP\nEstate of:\nof\npage\nLast Name\nFirst Name\nMiddle Name\nDocket No.\n, hereby certify that notice was given to each interested person as \nspecified below:\nI,\n(name)\nRETURN OF SERVICE\nTo:\nby\nfirst-class mail\nhand delivery\n(address)\nat:\n(date)\nOn:\nTo:\nby\nfirst-class mail\nhand delivery\n(address)\nat:\n(date)\nOn:\nTo:\nby\nfirst-class mail\nhand delivery\n(address)\nat:\n(date)\nOn:\nTo:\nby\nfirst-class mail\nhand delivery\n(address)\nat:\n(date)\nOn:\nclick to add\nclick to remove\nThe following interested persons have assented and waived notice and the assents and waivers are filed with \nthis Notice or are in the  \npossession of the Court:\nSIGNED UNDER THE PENALTIES OF PERJURY.\nPrimary Phone #: \n(Address)\n(Apt, Unit, No. etc.)\n(City/Town)\n(State)\n(Zip)\nPrimary Phone #: \n(Address)\n(Apt, Unit, No. etc.)\n(City/Town)\n(State)\n(Z"
